name: Bé Chuille

entities.type: group of Irish gods and goddesses

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.

attributes.attribute: only member of the Tuatha Dé Danann able to combat Carman

text: Irish mythology has a goddess named Bé Chuille (Becuille). She is known to be the magical daughter of the woodland goddess Flidais. Among the Tuatha Dé Danann, she is the only one who has the ability to fight against the evil sorceress Carman.
